title: Melbourne City FC A - League Women Hit Casey Fields
body_text:
Elite women's football returns to Casey Fields, with 7 matches locked in for the 2025/26 Ninja A-League Women's season.
Under Head Coach Michael Matricciani, Melbourne City FC will play the following matches at ctrl:cyber Pitch at the City Football Academy:
Saturday 8 November, 3:00 pm
Melbourne City FC V Central Coast Mariners FC
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-CCM26
Sunday 7 December, 3:00 pm
Melbourne City FC v Wellington Phoenix FC
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-WLPHX
Wednesday 17 December, 5:30 pm
Melbourne City FC v Adelaide United
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-ADLUTD26
Sunday 4 January, 5:00 pm
Melbourne City FC v Sydney FC
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-Sydfc
Wednesday 4 February, 5:30 pm
Melbourne City FC v Western Sydney Wanderers FC
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-WSWFC
Sunday 8 February, 5:00 PM
Melbourne City FC v Brisbane Roar FC
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-BR25
Sunday 15 March, 2:00 PM
Melbourne City FC V Canberra United FC
Tickets: https://events.ticketbooth.com.au/event/liberty-a-league-women-s-melbourne-city-fc-v-cnbu
After back-to-back Premiers Plate triumphs and a memorable run to last season's AFC Women's Champions League Final, everyone is welcome to come along and watch City's stars chase glory on home turf. So let's make some noise and show the rest of the league how Casey backs its football.
